===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|ic}}: two hands ({{zh-l|*廾}}) holding an object, perhaps a musical instrument used during a sacrifical ritual (the lower part of the object originally was similar to [[夲]]).

Otherwise, the whole character depicts two hands collecting resin ([[桼]]) dripping from a cut tree (drawn like [[屮]]). The resin is visible at the bottom of the character.

===Etymology===
Connected to {{och-l|走|to run}} by {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, though the Baxter-Sagart reconstruction of the Old pronunciations makes a connection less likely. Note, however, similarities to {{cog|my|ဆော့|t=to play, fiddle with}}.

